	<Title>
		Mood and food: Regain control
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Do you eat when you&apos;re not hungry? You might be indulging as a response to stress or boredom. Pay attention to when you eat and how you&apos;re feeling. If you turn to comfort foods out of habit rather than hunger, try a new tact. Instead of opening a bag of potato chips or unwrapping a candy bar, take a walk, listen to music or treat yourself to a movie.&lt;/p&gt;
